      • setAssociableTypes

        public CategoryTypes.UpdateSpec.Builder setAssociableTypes(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> associableTypes)
        Object types to which this category's tags can be attached.

        The Set of associable types cannot be updated incrementally. For example, if CategoryTypes.UpdateSpec.getAssociableTypes() originally contains {A,B,C} and you want to add D, then you need to pass {A,B,C,D} in your update specification. You also cannot remove any item from this Set. For example, if you have {A,B,C}, then you cannot remove say {A} from it. Similarly, if you start with an empty Set, then that implies that you can tag any object and hence you cannot later pass say {A}, because that would be restricting the type of objects you want to tag. Thus, associable types can only grow and not shrink.

        If null the associable types will not be modified.
        Parameters:
        associableTypes - New value for the property.
